==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snarling
<hw>Snarl"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from <er>Snarl</er>,
<pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Snarling iron</b></col>, <cd>a tool with a long beak,
used in the process of snarling. When one end is held in a vise, and the
shank is struck with a hammer, the repercussion of the other end, or
beak, within the article worked upon gives the requisite blow for
producing raised work. See 1st <er>Snarl</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snary</ent>⟦br⟧
